SUMMARY:Lifelong Adventure: Crystal Coast
DESCRIPTION:We’ll stay right on the beach for explorations of natural areas along the Crystal Coast\, also known as the Southern Banks. Short to moderate hikes in maritime forests\, tidal marshes\, Longleaf Pine forests and a rare limestone Bald Cypress swamp are all on the itinerary.\nHotel lodging reservation information will be emailed to registrants. \nPlease note: You will be required to enter the following information for each registrant before you can complete your registration: emergency contact\, physician contact and health information (allergies\, conditions\, medications relevant to this field experience). Take a moment to gather this information before beginning your registration. \nREGISTRATION FOR THIS TRIP IS FULL \nIf the trip is full\, please email Missy Chernick to be added to the waitlist. \nRegistration deadline: Tuesday\, March 10 at 10:00 AM \nFor additional information about this trip and other Lifelong Hikes & Adventures\, contact Jerry Reynolds at 919.707.9884.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/lifelong-adventure-crystal-coast-2/
LOCATION:In the Field
CATEGORIES:Adults,Lifelong Learners,Outdoor Experiences,Trips
END:VEVENT
