SUMMARY:The Key to Plant ID
DESCRIPTION:Scientists use tools called dichotomous keys to identify many species\, including plants. We’ll explore how to use and make keys in this interactive botany program. \nThis virtual program is especially for kids in grades K-8\, but everyone is welcome.  You do not need to join ecoEXPLORE before the program\, but should you choose to create an account for your child so they can get started documenting wildlife for scientists and earning prizes\, visit ecoexplore.net. \nRegister here
